      <h6>What is Organic</h6>
      <p>Organic produce is grown and processed without the use of   synthetic chemicals, fertilizers or GMOs with a focus on environmentally   sustainable practices.</p>
      <p>Organic systems are an innovative method of farming and   production focused on soil and land health, and balanced eco-systems.   Techniques used in organic agriculture deliver a diverse range of   benefits and their potential is increasingly being recognized in the   development of sustainable food and fiber technology for the future.</p>
      <p>Organic food and Organic cotton is not just chemical-free.   Organic farmers take a holistic approach to production and handling, and   the whole system is linked Soil, Plants, Animals, Food, People,   Environment, Health.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h6>Why Choose Certified Organic</h6>
      <p>Consumers cannot be guaranteed that a product is organic   unless it displays an organic certification logo such as the Global   Organic Textile Standard-GOTS logo/USDA etc.</p>
      <p>An organic certification logo protects consumers from   misleading claims and is the mark of a genuine organic product which has   been audited all along the production chain from paddock to plate to   comply with strict organic standards.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
